articles.text:
Viewers of the Big Brother Naija show have sympathized with Kayvee for withdrawing from the show.

Recall that Pere Pere, head of house announced Kayvee’s withdrawal on Monday while addressing the housemates

Kayvee withdrew from the show due to health reasons.

Pere had said: “Please be advised that kayvee will no longer be on this show due to his health.”

Biggie, however, asked the housemates to help Kayvee pack his bags.

Reacting Nigerians on social media prayed and wished him well.

See reactions below;

@Rima, “ This house if you are not mentally strong it will break you. I really liked Kayvee was really rooting for him. I pray he gets better.“

@Stellabuz, “ KayVee, thanks for choosing ur health over the show and the money. Once you are back in good strength & health, trust me, you will get lots of Photography gigs.

Don’t stress yourself at all. We will recommend more gigs for you. Stay safe, and God be with you, Kayvee.”

@Kamvoo, “ I think kayvee made the best choice. we wish him the best and we love him regardless.”

@mztiquee, “ The show really takes its toll on these housemates. I wish Kayvee all the best.”

@sowtz, “ sending love to him Black people we need to really look into our mental health.”

@Sasforce, “ We missed out on such an awesome personality on our screen. It will get better from here Kayvee, just focus on getting well. “

@avenuecyprus, “ Sad day in #BBNaija, it’s always sad when a housemate has to withdraw from the show due to ill health. I wish you well #kayvee . Get well soon. I shall miss your voice in the house. May you grow in your work outside the house.”

@oluwatosyn, “ Kayvee was definitely going through something before the show. This show is meant to be fun and enjoyable (at least while in the house) not drive you into depression.”

@adekoya, “ Really sad about ds guy KayVee guy, may God see him through. This is what Erica Nlewedim went thru & more last year, she asked to talk to a professional & she was denied. They want my favorite to lose her mind. A show as big as #BBNajia should have professionals housemates can talk to.”

@sanmek, “ We are proud of you KayVee. You are a winner no matter what, don’t dim your light young man. The Lord’s got you. Lots of love from SA.”

DailyPost
